#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="pli"><section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Bhūtagāmavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 12"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "12. Aññavādakasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on evasive speech"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs0.6"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.12.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.230"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa350"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Kosambī in Ghosita’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā channo anācāraṃ ācaritvā saṃghamajjhe āpattiyā "
"anuyuñjīyamāno aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati—Then, when he was examined about an "
"offense in the midst of the Order, he spoke evasively,"
msgstr ""
"At that time Venerable Channa was misbehaving. Then, when he was examined "
"about an offense in the midst of the Order, he spoke evasively,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.3"
msgid ""
"“ko āpanno, kiṃ āpanno, kismiṃ āpanno, kathaṃ āpanno, kaṃ bhaṇatha, kiṃ "
"bhaṇathā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Who has committed an offense? What offense has been committed? In regard to "
"what has an offense has been committed? How has an offense been committed? "
"Who are you talking about? What are you talking about?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.36"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa351"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.6"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma āyasmā channo saṃghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno aññenaññaṃ "
"paṭicarissati—"
msgstr ""
"“How can Venerable Channa speak evasively in this way when he is examined "
"about an offense in the midst of the Order?’”…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.7"
msgid ""
"‘ko āpanno, kiṃ āpanno, kismiṃ āpanno, kathaṃ āpanno, kaṃ bhaṇatha, kiṃ "
"bhaṇathā’”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.8"
msgid ""
"saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, channa, saṃghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno aññenaññaṃ "
"paṭicarasi—‘"
msgstr "“Is it true, Channa, that you are speaking like this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.9"
msgid ""
"ko āpanno, kiṃ āpanno, kismiṃ āpanno, kathaṃ āpanno, kaṃ bhaṇatha, kiṃ "
"bhaṇathā’”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.12"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, saṃghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno "
"aññenaññaṃ paṭicarissasi—"
msgstr ""
"Foolish man, when examined about an offense in the midst of the Order, how "
"can you speak evasively, thus:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.13"
msgid ""
"“ko āpanno, kiṃ āpanno, kismiṃ āpanno, kathaṃ āpanno, kaṃ bhaṇatha, kiṃ "
"bhaṇathā”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Who has committed an offense? What offense has been committed? In regard to "
"what has an offense has been committed? How has an offense been committed? "
"Who are you talking about? What are you talking about?’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …”…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "vigarahitvā … pe …"
msgstr "and after criticizing him …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "he gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṃgho channassa bhikkhuno aññavādakaṃ ropetu."
msgstr "“Well then, monks, let the Order charge Channa with evasive speech."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, ropetabbaṃ."
msgstr "And he is to be charged in this way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṃgho ñāpetabbo—"
msgstr "A competent and capable monk should inform the Order:"

#. </p><div class="kamma"><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.231"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa352"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.21"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu saṃghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno aññenaññaṃ "
"paṭicarati."
msgstr ""
"This monk Channa speaks evasively when examined about an offense in the "
"midst of the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.22"
msgid ""
"Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho channassa bhikkhuno aññavādakaṃ ropeyya."
msgstr ""
"If it seems appropriate to the Order, the Order should charge him with "
"evasive speech."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.23"
msgid "Esā ñatti."
msgstr "This is the motion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa353"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.24"
msgid "Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.25"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu saṃghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno aññenaññaṃ "
"paṭicarati."
msgstr ""
"This monk Channa speaks evasively when examined about an offense in the "
"midst of the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.26"
msgid "Saṃgho channassa bhikkhuno aññavādakaṃ ropeti."
msgstr "The Order is charging him of evasive speech."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.27"
msgid ""
"Yassāyasmato khamati channassa bhikkhuno aññavādakassa ropanā, so tuṇhassa;"
msgstr ""
"Any monk who approves of charging him of evasive speech should remain silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.28"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should say so."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa354"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.29"
msgid "Ropitaṃ saṃghena channassa bhikkhuno aññavādakaṃ."
msgstr "The Order has charged the monk Channa of evasive speech."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.30"
msgid "Khamati saṃghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti."
msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”"

#. </p></div><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa355"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.31"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ channaṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya "
"… pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing Channa in many ways for being difficult to support …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.32"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr ""
"the Master said, “And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.32a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa356"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.33"
msgid "“Aññavādake pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk speaks evasively, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa357"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs1.34"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.12.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa358"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā channo saṃghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno "
"aññenaññaṃ paṭicaranto—"
msgstr ""
"Later, when Channa was again being examined about an offense in the midst of "
"the Order, he thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "“āpattiṃ āpajjissāmī”ti tuṇhībhūto saṃghaṃ viheseti."
msgstr ""
"“By speaking evasively I’ll commit an offenses,” and he instead harassed the "
"Order by remaining silent."

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.4"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.5"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma āyasmā channo saṃghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno tuṇhībhūto "
"saṃghaṃ vihesessatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“When he’s examined about an offense in the midst of the Order, how can "
"Venerable Channa harass the Order by remaining silent?’”…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.6"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, channa, saṃghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno tuṇhībhūto "
"saṃghaṃ vihesesī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Channa, that you are acting like this?”"

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.232"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.9"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, saṃghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno "
"tuṇhībhūto saṃghaṃ vihesessasi."
msgstr ""
"Foolish man, when you are examined about an offense in the midst of the "
"Order, how can you harass the Order by remaining silent?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …”…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "vigarahitvā … pe …"
msgstr "and after criticizing him …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "he gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.13"
msgid "“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṃgho channassa bhikkhuno vihesakaṃ ropetu."
msgstr "“Well then, monks, let the Order charge Channa of harassment."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.14"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, ropetabbaṃ."
msgstr "And he is to be charged in this way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.15"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṃgho ñāpetabbo—"
msgstr "A competent and capable monk should inform the Order:"

#. </p><div class="kamma"><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa359"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.16"
msgid "‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.17"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu saṃghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno tuṇhībhūto saṃghaṃ "
"viheseti."
msgstr ""
"This monk Channa, when examined about an offense in the midst of the Order, "
"harasses the Order by remaining silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.18"
msgid ""
"Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho channassa bhikkhuno vihesakaṃ ropeyya."
msgstr ""
"If it seems appropriate to the Order, the Order should charge him of "
"harassment."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.19"
msgid "Esā ñatti."
msgstr "This is the motion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa360"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.20"
msgid "Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.21"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu saṃghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno tuṇhībhūto saṃghaṃ "
"viheseti."
msgstr ""
"This monk Channa, when examined about an offense in the midst of the Order, "
"harasses the Order by remaining silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.22"
msgid "Saṃgho channassa bhikkhuno vihesakaṃ ropeti."
msgstr "The Order is charging him of harassment."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.23"
msgid ""
"Yassāyasmato khamati channassa bhikkhuno vihesakassa ropanā, so tuṇhassa;"
msgstr ""
"Any monk who approves of charging him of harassment should remain silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.24"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should say so."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa361"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.25"
msgid "Ropitaṃ saṃghena channassa bhikkhuno vihesakaṃ."
msgstr "The Order has charged the monk Channa of harassment."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.26"
msgid "Khamati saṃghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti."
msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”"

#. </p></div><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa362"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.27"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ channaṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya "
"… pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing Channa in many ways for being difficult to support …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.28"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr ""
"the Master said, “And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.28a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa363"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.29"
msgid "“Aññavādake vihesake pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk speaks evasively or harasses, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs2.30"
msgid "(<em>12</em>:<strong>61</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.37"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.12.3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.12.3.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa364"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.1.1"
msgid "Aññavādako nāma"
msgstr "One who speaks evasively:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.1.2"
msgid ""
"saṃghamajjhe vatthusmiṃ vā āpattiyā vā anuyuñjīyamāno taṃ na kathetukāmo taṃ "
"na ugghāṭetukāmo aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati—"
msgstr ""
"when being examined in the midst of the Order about an action that was the "
"basis for an offense or about the class of an offense, he speaks evasively "
"because he does not want to talk about it or reveal it, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.1.3"
msgid ""
"“ko āpanno, kiṃ āpanno, kismiṃ āpanno, kathaṃ āpanno, kaṃ bhaṇatha, kiṃ "
"bhaṇathā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Who has committed an offense? What offense has been committed? In regard to "
"what has an offense has been committed? How has an offense been committed? "
"Who are you talking about? What are you talking about?”—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.1.4"
msgid "Eso aññavādako nāma."
msgstr "this is called “one who speaks evasively.”"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa365"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.1.5"
msgid "Vihesako nāma"
msgstr "One who harasses:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.1.6"
msgid ""
"saṃghamajjhe vatthusmiṃ vā āpattiyā vā anuyuñjīyamāno taṃ na kathetukāmo taṃ "
"na ugghāṭetukāmo tuṇhībhūto saṃghaṃ viheseti."
msgstr ""
"when being examined in the midst of the Order about an action that was the "
"basis for an offense or about the class of an offense, he harasses the Order "
"by remaining silent because he does not want to talk about it or reveal it—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.1.7"
msgid "Eso vihesako nāma."
msgstr "this is called “one who harasses.”"

#. </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.1.7a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa366"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.1.8"
msgid ""
"Aropite aññavādake saṃghamajjhe vatthusmiṃ vā āpattiyā vā anuyuñjīyamāno taṃ "
"na kathetukāmo taṃ na ugghāṭetukāmo aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati—"
msgstr ""
"If he has not been charged with evasive speech, but he is being examined in "
"the midst of the Order about an action that was the basis for an offense or "
"about the class of an offense, and he then speaks evasively because he does "
"not want to talk about it or reveal it, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.1.9"
msgid ""
"“ko āpanno, kiṃ āpanno, kismiṃ āpanno, kathaṃ āpanno, kaṃ bhaṇatha, kiṃ "
"bhaṇathā”ti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"“Who has committed an offense? What offense has been committed? In regard to "
"what has an offense has been committed? How has an offense been committed? "
"Who are you talking about? What are you talking about?” then he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.233"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.1.10"
msgid ""
"Aropite vihesake saṃghamajjhe vatthusmiṃ vā āpattiyā vā anuyuñjīyamāno taṃ "
"na kathetukāmo taṃ na ugghāṭetukāmo tuṇhībhūto saṃghaṃ viheseti, āpatti "
"dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he has not been charged with harassment, but he is being examined in the "
"midst of the Order about an action that was the basis for an offense or "
"about the class of an offense, and he then harasses the Order by remaining "
"silent because he does not want to talk about it or reveal it, then he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.1.11"
msgid ""
"Ropite aññavādake saṃghamajjhe vatthusmiṃ vā āpattiyā vā anuyuñjīyamāno taṃ "
"na kathetukāmo taṃ na ugghāṭetukāmo aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati—"
msgstr ""
"If he has been charged with evasive speech, and he is being examined in the "
"midst of the Order about an action that was the basis for an offense or "
"about the class of an offense, and he then speaks evasively because he does "
"not want to talk about it or reveal it, saying,"

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.1.12"
msgid ""
"“ko āpanno, kiṃ āpanno, kismiṃ āpanno, kathaṃ āpanno, kaṃ bhaṇatha, kiṃ "
"bhaṇathā”ti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"“Who has committed an offense? What offense has been committed? In regard to "
"what has an offense has been committed? How has an offense been committed? "
"Who are you talking about? What are you talking about?” then he commits an "
"offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.1.13"
msgid ""
"Ropite vihesake saṃghamajjhe vatthusmiṃ vā āpattiyā vā anuyuñjīyamāno taṃ na "
"kathetukāmo taṃ na ugghāṭetukāmo tuṇhībhūto saṃghaṃ viheseti, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he has been charged with harassment, and he is being examined in the "
"midst of the Order about an action that was the basis for an offense or "
"about the class of an offense, and he then harasses the Order by remaining "
"silent because he does not want to talk about it or reveal it, then he "
"commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.12.3.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa367"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.2.1"
msgid "Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññī aññavādake vihesake, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a legitimate procedure, and he perceives it as legitimate, and he "
"speaks evasively and he harasses, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.2.2"
msgid "Dhammakamme vematiko aññavādake vihesake, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a legitimate procedure, but he is unsure if it is, and he speaks "
"evasively and he harasses, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.2.3"
msgid "Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññī aññavādake vihesake, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a legitimate procedure, but he perceives it as illegitimate, and he "
"speaks evasively and he harasses, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.2.4"
msgid "Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure, but he perceives it as legitimate, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.2.5"
msgid "Adhammakamme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.2.6"
msgid "Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure, and he perceives it as illegitimate, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.12.3.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa368"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.3.2"
msgid "ajānanto pucchati,"
msgstr "if he asks because he does not know;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.3.3"
msgid "gilāno vā na katheti;"
msgstr "if he does not speak because he is sick;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.3.4"
msgid ""
"“saṃghassa bhaṇḍanaṃ vā kalaho vā viggaho vā vivādo vā bhavissatī”ti na "
"katheti;"
msgstr ""
"if he does not speak because he thinks there will be quarreling or disputing "
"in the Order;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.3.5"
msgid "“saṃghabhedo vā saṃgharāji vā bhavissatī”ti na katheti;"
msgstr ""
"if he does not speak because he thinks there will be fracture or schism in "
"the Order;"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.234"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.3.6"
msgid ""
"“adhammena vā vaggena vā nakammārahassa vā kammaṃ karissatī”ti na katheti;"
msgstr ""
"if he does not speak because he thinks the procedure will be illegitimate, "
"done by an incomplete assembly, or done to one who is not subject to a "
"procedure;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.3.7"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.3.8"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa369"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc12:pts-cs3.3.9"
msgid "Aññavādakasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ."
msgstr "The second rule, the training rule on evasive speech, is finished."

